# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Velora Agroprocessing Ltd. static HTML website.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Created**: `package.json` - Project manifest with `@vercel/speed-insights` dependency (v1.3.1)
- **Created**: `package-lock.json` - Lockfile for consistent dependency resolution
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package using npm

### 2. Speed Insights Integration
- **Created**: `speed-insights.js` - Initialization script that:
  - Sets up the Speed Insights queue (window.si and window.siq)
  - Dynamically loads the Speed Insights script from Vercel's CDN (`/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js`)
  - Uses deferred loading to avoid blocking page rendering

### 3. HTML Updates
Modified all 11 HTML pages to include the Speed Insights script:
- `index.html`
- `about.html`
- `products.html`
- `shop.html`
- `careers.html`
- `contact.html`
- `distribution.html`
- `impact.html`
- `investors.html`
- `news.html`
- `reviews.html`

Each file now includes `<script src="speed-insights.js"></script>` in the `<head>` section.

### 4. Git Configuration
- **Created**: `.gitignore` - Ensures node_modules and other build artifacts are not committed

## Implementation Approach

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I implemented the static HTML/vanilla JavaScript approach:

1. The script initializes the Speed Insights queue using the recommended pattern
2. It dynamically loads the tracking script from Vercel's CDN path
3. The script is included in all HTML pages for comprehensive tracking

## How It Works

When the website is deployed to Vercel:
- The Speed Insights script will automatically load from `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js`
- It will track Web Vitals metrics (LCP, FID, CLS, TTFB, INP)
- Metrics will be sent to Vercel's Speed Insights dashboard
- Data collection only occurs in production (not in development mode)

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Ensure Speed Insights is enabled in the Vercel project dashboard
2. After a few days of traffic, metrics will be visible in the Speed Insights dashboard
3. Monitor Core Web Vitals to identify performance improvement opportunities

## Notes

- Speed Insights will only function when deployed to Vercel (not in local development)
- The implementation follows the official vanilla JavaScript pattern for static sites
- All HTML files maintain their original structure with only the script tag addition
- The package.json allows for future npm-based tooling if needed
